<h2>API Key</h2>
<ul>
<li>The API key <strong>must</strong> be obtained <strong>exclusively</strong> from the environment variable <code>process.env.API_KEY</code>. Assume this variable is pre-configured, valid, and accessible in the execution context where the API client is initialized.</li>
<li>Use this <code>process.env.API_KEY</code> string <strong>directly</strong> when initializing the <code>@google/genai</code> client instance (must use <code>new GoogleGenAI({ apiKey: process.env.API_KEY })</code>).</li>
<li>Do <strong>not</strong> generate any UI elements (input fields, forms, prompts, configuration sections) or code snippets for entering or managing the API key. Do <strong>not</strong> define <code>process.env</code> or request that the user update the API_KEY in the code. The key's availability is handled externally and is a hard requirement. The application <strong>must not</strong> ask the user for it under any circumstances.</li>
</ul>
